\subsubsection{Nearest Neighbor Recognition}
For k-NN evaluation, we apply a very simple method following the protocol of DINO: we run all the dataset through the backbone to collect the class tokens, perform L2-normalization, retrieve the k closest neighbors in terms of cosine similarities in the training set for each sample of the validation set, and apply a softmax with a fixed temperature of 0.07 for voting. We use $k = 10$ and show results in Table~\ref{tab:knn-inet1k}.

