%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% OPEN VOCAB %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\subsubsection{Open Vocabulary Evaluation}
% \pb{POC: Alaa. Question : do we keep it for the supmat?}
Pretraining self-supervised features without using ImageNet allows to evaluate their ability at zero-shot classification on this benchmark.
To probe their quality in this setting, we train a text encoder on top of our frozen features using the LAION dataset.
Note that we do not finetune our visual features.
We compare with several recent methods based on CLIP that learn features with a text-guided objective. 
Most of these methods differs in larger and new architectures, as well as the use of large private text-image datasets.
As shown in Table~\ref{tab:zs-inet1k}, our features works reasonably well in this setting and achieve comparable performance with other features trained on LAION.

