%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% FINEGRAINED %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\subsection{Fine-grained Classification}
For the fine-grained classification, we follow the protocol defined in \cite{chen2020simple}, section B.8.1: we employ an off-the-shelf logistic regression classifier (from the scikit-learn library \cite{scikit-learn}) on the class tokens for the datasets being evaluated. We use 10k iterations, and a C regularizer in a logspace range of 45 values spanning from  $10^{-6}$ to $10^{5}$. We transform the images with a resize to 224 pixels along the shorter side followed by a 224 × 224 center crop. For datasets that possess a validation set, we used it to select the value of C, then trained on the train and validation sets to evaluate on the test set. For other datasets, we replaced the validation set by 10\% of the train set. On DTD and SUN397, we report results only for the first split. Results are shown in Table~\ref{tab:finegrained} in the main text.
